retweeted_text:
American taxpayers invested ~$70mm in the development of remdesivir, now used to treat covid-19.

Gilead Pharmaceuticals is charging ~$3,000/patient for a drug that costs ~$10 to produce and for which we have no ability to negotiate.

Unacceptable.

 https://t.co/Tb5AhwisqB

retweeted_text: Moving toward a greener future is critical to fighting climate change. Last year, @RepHarley, @RepDeSaulnier, and I introduced legislation to install electric and hydrogen fueling stations along U.S. highways. I'm proud that our bill was included in the Moving Forward Act. (4/4)

full_text: I just voted to pass the #MovingForward Act, a bill that empowers businesses and creates jobs for working families — all while addressing the climate crisis. With the help of my amendments, H.R. 2 will deliver common-sense solutions that invest in our local communities. https://t.co/PXbPGbQ5CX

My House #OrangeCounty colleagues and I sent a letter to @ochealth requesting more info on Orange County's low #COVID_19 testing volume in comparison to other counties.

We need to understand the factors contributing to the deficiency if we are to better address the disparity. https://t.co/HEybsQ3bX2

We need a nationwide moratorium on utility shut-offs. 

Running water is necessary to wash hands and disinfect surfaces. Electricity keeps food safe and the lights on. Internet service enables kids to participate in distance learning.

A math lesson for @realDonaldTrump:

The United States is ~4.25% of the world's population. 
~30% of global #COVID19 cases are in the United States & ~20% of global #COVID19 deaths are in the United States

That doesn't add up to equal a "perfect" response.

full_text:
On #WorldHealthDay, health care professionals are on the frontlines of the #COVID19 crisis, working without personal protective equipment. 

Thanking nurses & doctors isn't enough. We need to get them #PPE — NOW.

UPDATE: CA has tested almost 67,000 people for #COVID19. 

2535 have tested positive. 37 of those were people under 17. 51% were between ages of 18-49.

This disease can impact anyone. Stay home. Practice social and physical distancing. Take this seriously.

House Democrats negotiated a bipartisan $8.3 billion #coronavirus supplemental—including $3 billion for research, $7 billion for small businesses and $2 billion for public health funding—to address this crisis HEAD ON.

We will ALWAYS keep our nation safe. #ForThePeople https://t.co/uYHqMI0LZQ

We must continue to hold industry accountable for poisoning our oceans, land, air, and drinking water.

full_text:
11 years ago, the #LillyLedbetter Fair Pay Act, which recognized gendered wage discrimination, was signed into law. 

Today, women STILL do not receive equal pay for equal work. It's time for the Senate to pass the #PaycheckFairnessAct.

Orange County is grieving, but we will find solace and purpose in the example they left behind and the belief in something bigger than ourselves.

full_text: Our community lost kids who were overflowing with promise. Kids who were great competitors and even better friends. Kids you could count on - on and off the court. Kids who pushed themselves to be more and were the best daughters that any parent could ask for.

full_text:
Remember their names. 

Alyssa, Keri + John Altobelli 
Gianna + Kobe Bryant
Payton + Sarah Chester
Christina Mauser
Ara Zobayan

They were all connected by a love of the game. A steadfast belief in sports being bigger than a score - more than just an hour or two on the court.

Happy #KoreanAmericanDay! Today marks the arrival of the first Korean immigrants to the US. 

Korean Americans are an integral part of our nation - chasing/achieving the American dream. 

We’re all better for the rich culture & community brought to our shores 117 years ago.

Clearly, all eyes in DC this week were on the E&C markup that passed 18 bills to address:

🚭Youth tobacco epidemic
🤱Maternity care
🧪Toxic chemicals
⚠️Safer pipelines
📡Secure communications networks
🗺️Broadband maps
🕵️‍♂️Web scams
✈️Tourism

See what you missed in 60 seconds 👇 https://t.co/psLtz02t8G

full_text: I look forward to receiving a robust response from the EPA, showing their work to protect families across the United States. If the EPA ignores our request, I will use every tool necessary to demand transparency on behalf of the American people. https://t.co/eezcynwjBj (4/4)

full_text:
A human being who isn’t and will never be perfect – none of us are.

@RepKatieHill acknowledged her errors in judgement and is resigning because she values integrity, decency, and accountability – I can’t say the same about several of our colleagues. (2/x)

full_text:
Today is #NationalFirstRespondersDay

DYK? Thousands of first responders are left without affordable health care coverage when they retire. 

My bill would allow them to buy into Medicare before age 65, ensuring they have access to the care they deserve. https://t.co/NuQ5ejuUuE

retweeted_text: One year ago at the Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh, 11 people lost their lives in a horrific mass shooting. Today, we honor their memory as we work to end gun violence, speak out against anti-Semitism and those who enable it, and make these tragedies a thing of the past.

full_text:
Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi was evil personified. His terrorist organization made our world a darker place. 

Thanks to our brave special forces and intelligence personnel - the world is a safer, better place today.

I will continue to fight for press freedom in Jamal's memory and for all journalists who face threats across the globe. https://t.co/8LOHHZLqGu

🗸 Introduced a bill to expand health care for first responders
🗸 Moved my bill holding chemical companies accountable for #PFAS contamination to @EnergyCommerce 
🗸 Upheld my constitutional duty by calling for your impeachment https://t.co/e1CNt5W9Sf

retweeted_text:
When the history books are written about this tumultuous era, I want them to show that I was among those in the House of Representatives who stood up to lawlessness and tyranny.

Read my statement supporting impeachment: https://t.co/xppt73HN6k

full_text:
Thanks to all who have contacted my office in response to my impeachment position. 

However, I don't need your thanks. Protecting the Constitution is something ALL Members of Congress swore to do. 

I hope my colleagues on the other side of the aisle will uphold that oath.

retweeted_text: "I’m talking about the right to feel safe when we walk outside or turn on our faucets... and this safety is not and should never be contingent upon where we live, the color of our skin, our income bracket, our party affiliation." -@RepHarley on #EnvironmentalJustice

full_text:
We are here today not just to talk about clean air and clean water and equal access to our natural resources—we are here to remind ourselves what kind of country we want to be. 

Watch my @OversightDems hearing LIVE: https://t.co/NgKRtuphZh https://t.co/ojhJszPGbs

Yesterday I had the opportunity to thank @RepHarley for his incredible work to #ProtectOurCare

I testified before him on July 10th for healthcare. 

The Congressman cares deeply!

We have a video forthcoming on how crucial it is to sign up for open enrollment for the ACA. https://t.co/Vpv8R5XJUG

. @RepHarley's opening statement:

Congratulations to Fountain Valley Living on 11 years - here's to many more! https://t.co/BfU8ykCr55

PFAS has contaminated our water, our air, our way of life. It's clear we need to know the extent of contamination & accountability.

These are questions we all need answers to at today’s hearing. https://t.co/ZBwwRE5eC5

retweeted_text:
.@RepHarley Rouda: "We want to make sure the dollars are being properly utilized, on one hand. On the other hand, we want to make sure we're sharing across communities that are being affected the most by the opioid crisis."
https://t.co/dtJCjxUi5k

full_text: Thank you to @RepTimBurchett, and several of my colleagues for supporting the Effective Drug Control Strategy Act and ensuring our fight against the addiction crisis is waged strategically and effectively. (4/4)

full_text: This year, Americans will lose close to 70,000 friends, family, and loved ones to drug-related deaths. My bill, the Effective Drug Control Strategy Act, is a small but significant step to improve the effectiveness of our fight against the addiction crisis. (1/x)

Today marks the 4th anniversary of the devastating tragedy that was the Emanuel AME Church shooting. 

While we offer our thoughts and prayers to the families and victims of that day, we also ought to be taking action. 

The House has acted. It’s the Senate’s turn. https://t.co/vGwqt0J7UW

full_text: I'm proud to represent a thriving Southeast Asian community full of men and women who fled violence during and after the Vietnam War, in search of a better life. My amendment recognizes their contributions and discourages attempts to repatriate them. https://t.co/ic6SYmKpco

retweeted_text: .@RepHarley: Couldn't we identify 100s of eligible storage sites and use a market-based process to narrow them down, instead of "putting all our eggs in one basket" at Yucca Mountain?

full_text:
There are now approximately 100 sites across at least 34 states currently storing high-level nuclear waste. We need safe spent fuel solutions NOW. 
Watch our @OversightDems hearing live: https://t.co/Zf9SbzZBLG https://t.co/SQwIawvVmX

🔹Near earthquake fault lines 
🔹100 feet from the Pacific Ocean

Enough is enough.

full_text:
If climate change was an adversarial nation who planned to kill millions by:

- Jeopardizing clean drinking water/destroying crops
- Demolishing coastal property
- Releasing dormant viruses

We would already be at war. 

On #EarthDay, and every day, let's fight climate change.

It's a staggering reminder of what we stand to lose if we don't act on the Climate Crisis before it's too late. https://t.co/OL5NEi5gW2

-HR

Today Michael Cohen told me that convicted Russian mobster Felix Sater occupied an office on Trump's floor, the same one Cohen himself later moved into. 
I asked: Based on those facts, isn’t it true that Donald Trump misled at best, or at worst lied under oath?
Michael Cohen: Yes https://t.co/5ayhTVjM3c

“Is it true that President Trump lied under oath?”
“Yes”

Democrat Harley Rouda pushes Donald Trump's ex-lawyer Michael Cohen on the US President's links with "convicted Russian mobster Felix Sater"

#CohenTestimony latest: https://t.co/3J9nebR2wm https://t.co/1ql8IoI2uO

full_text:
Congress doesn’t block for the President. We serve the American people. 

Why have my Republican colleagues failed to ask even one question about Trump’s activities? If we seek the truth, what are they afraid we’ll find?

This committee’s job is oversight, time to clock in.

full_text: Today I met with @MFOLDC and @Team_Enough. The anniversary of the Parkland shooting is two days away– and nearly 1200 kids have died from gun violence in a year of Congressional inaction. It's past time to pass H.R. 8 and expand background checks, and that’s just the first step. https://t.co/O8UDGC1hKh

retweeted_text: "The Supreme Court's #CitizensUnited decision said that corporations are people too. Personally I've never held hands with a corporation. We know that dark money leads to undue influence at best & at worst, outright corruption."—@RepHarley at the @OversightDems' #HR1 hearing

full_text: This morning I rose in response to the #SOTU “We should not wait for, nor expect, the president to lead an agenda for the people. But we can move forward...and work with one another, regardless of party, to improve the lives of the people who trusted us to represent them” https://t.co/QUKuc6Jx2X
